    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The technique of dropping or painting acid onto an aquatint ground to allow localized and controlled biting. To control the acid application, traditionally, a clean brush was coated with saliva, dipped into nitric acid, and brushed onto the ground.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
